Detailed Description

This header defines GTI APIs and definitions either used internally and not available or GTI APIs that should not be used by the GTI client.

Copyright (c) 1998-2015, Texas Instruments Inc., All rights reserved.

enum EXE_STATE

Private.

Execution state flags used internally by router control code.

Enumerator:
EXE_STATE_UNKNOWN 

Unknown execution mode.

EXE_STATE_HALT 

Halt mode.

EXE_STATE_STEP 

Single step mode.

EXE_STATE_RUN_DBG 

Debug run mode (normal run).

EXE_STATE_RUN_FREE 

Non-debug run mode (run free).

EXE_STATE_RUN_LOWPWR 

Low power run mode.

enum GTI_BLKRST_CMD_TYPE

GTI_STRING_TYPE  pathName,
GTI_PORT_TYPE  portAddress,
GTI_STRING_TYPE  parmFileName,
GTI_PORT_TYPE  portAddress2,
GTI_DMA_TYPE  dmaAddress,
GTI_IRQ_TYPE  irq,
GTI_HANDLE_TYPE *  hpid,
GTI_ADDRS_TYPE *  options,
GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hPrivateData 
)

Do_Initialization() - Private.

Initialize the debug session.

Called by GTI_INIT_EX().

Returns:
0 on success, -1 on error. On success, new instance handle is returned in the *hpid parameter.
Parameters:
[in]procNumProcessor number (unused).
[in]pathNameDebug probe and target name \ cpu name.
[in]portAddressDebug probe port address (unused).
[in]parmFileNamePath and name of board config file.
[in]portAddress2Alternate debug probe port address (unused).
[in]dmaAddressDebug probe DMA address (unused).
[in]irqDebug probe IRQ number (unused).
[out]hpidGTI API instance handle.
[in]optionsOptions flags (unused).
[in]hPrivateDataAdditional setup information.
